### **Variables**

First, here are some primitive data types:

- int var; // 4 bytes of memory - range from -2147483648 to +2147483647
- char var; // 1 byte of memory (8 bits) - range from -128 to 127 or 0 to 255
- bool var; // either true(1) or false(0)
- float var; // 4 bytes of memory - used to store single precision floating pt values or decimal values
- double var; // 8 bytes of memory - used to store double precision floating pt values or decimal values
- void; // takes no space and returns no value - used for functions that do not return any value
- wchar_t var; // 2 or 4 bytes of memory - used for character data types that have size > 1 byte

Second, here are data type modifiers:

- signed       | (int, char, long prefix)
- unsigned     | (int, char, short prefix)
- short        | (int)
- long         | (int, double)

